{{Infobox football biography |name = Juninho Bacuna |fullname = Juninho Bacuna |image = Juninho bacuna-1531777726.jpeg |birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1997|8|7|df=y}} |birth_place = [[Groningen]], Netherlands |height = {{convert|1.78|m|order=flip}}<ref>{{Cite web |title=Juninho Bacuna |publisher=Huddersfield Town A.F.C. |accessdate=14 September 2018 |url= https://www.htafc.com/matches/first-team/midfielder/juninho-bacuna/}}</ref> |position = [[Midfielder#Central midfielder|Central midfielder]] |currentclub = [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]] |clubnumber = 7 |youthyears1 = –2005 |youthclubs1 = FC Lewenborg |youthyears2 = 2005–2006 |youthclubs2 = GRC Groningen |youthyears3 = 2006–2015 |youthclubs3 = [[FC Groningen|Groningen]] |years1 = 2015–2018 |clubs1 = [[FC Groningen|Groningen]] |years2 = 2018– |clubs2 = [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]] |caps1 = 82 |goals1 = 2 |caps2 = 12 |goals2 = 1 | nationalyears1 = 2015–2016 | nationalteam1 = Netherlands U18 | nationalcaps1 = 2 | nationalgoals1 = 0 | nationalyears2 = 2016–2018 | nationalteam2 = Netherlands U20 | nationalcaps2 = 11 | nationalgoals2 = 0 | nationalyears3 = 2018– | nationalteam3 = [[Netherlands national under-21 football team|Netherlands U21]] | nationalcaps3 = 3 | nationalgoals3 = 2 |pcupdate = 22:22, 26 February 2019 (UTC) |nationalteam-update = 21:20, 29 May 2018 (UTC) }}
'''Juninho Bacuna''' (born 7 August 1997) is a Dutch professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Midfielder#Central midfielder|central midfielder]] for [[Premier League]] side [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]] and the [[Netherlands national under-21 football team|Netherlands national under-21 team]].
==Club career== ===Groningen=== Bacuna is a [[FC Groningen|Groningen]] youth exponent. He made his [[Eredivisie]] debut on 5 February 2015 against [[Heracles Almelo]] replacing [[Yoell van Nieff]] after 79 minutes in a 2–2 away draw.<ref name="soccerway2">{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2015/02/05/netherlands/eredivisie/stichting-heracles-almelo/stichting-fc-groningen/1690849/|title=Heracles Almelo vs. FC Groningen - 5 February 2015 - Soccerway|publisher=soccerway.com|accessdate=2015-03-08}}</ref> He came off the bench to help the Green-White Army win the [[KNVB Cup]] in 2014/15 against defending champions [[PEC Zwolle]]. It was their first major trophy and they qualified for the [[UEFA Europa League]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Groningen claim first trophy with KNVB Cup triumph|url=http://www.goal.com/en/news/462/netherlands/2015/05/04/11389992/groningen-claim-first-trophy-with-knvb-cup-triumph|accessdate=18 May 2015|work=Goal.com|date=4 May 2015}}</ref><ref>https://za.soccerway.com/matches/2015/05/03/netherlands/knvb-beker/bvo-fc-zwolle/stichting-fc-groningen/2028581/</ref>
===Huddersfield Town=== Bacuna signed for [[Premier League]] team [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]] on 20 June 2018, for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.skysports.com/football/news/11095/11410829/huddersfield-sign-juninho-bacuna-from-fc-groningen|title=Huddersfield sign Juninho Bacuna from FC Groningen|work=Sky Sports|access-date=2018-06-21|language=en}}</ref>
==Personal life== He is the younger brother of [[Leandro Bacuna]], also a footballer.<ref>{{cite web|title=Ook tweede Bacuna wint de beker|trans-title=Second Bacuna wins the cup as well|url=http://nos.nl/artikel/2036079-ook-tweede-bacuna-wint-de-beker.html|accessdate=6 November 2015|publisher=[[Nederlandse Omroep Stichting]]|date=17 May 2015|language=Dutch}}</ref>
