{{Infobox football biography | name = Adama Diakhaby | image = Stade rennais vs USM Alger, July 16th 2016 - Adama Diakhaby 1.jpg | caption = Diakhaby in 2016 | fullname = Adama Salimou Diakhaby<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thefa.com/-/media/files/thefaportal/governance-docs/registrations/july-2018.ashx |title=List of Players under Written Contract Registered Between 01/07/2018 and 31/07/2018 |publisher=The Football Association |format=PDF |page=10 |accessdate=2 February 2019}}</ref> | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1996|7|5|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Ajaccio]], France | height = 1.84 m | position = [[Left winger]] | currentclub = [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]] | clubnumber = 11 | youthyears1 = 2003–2004 | youthclubs1 = AJ Biguglia | youthyears2 = 2004 | youthclubs2 = Saint-Étienne du Rouvray | youthyears3 = 2004–2005 | youthclubs3 = AJ Biguglia | youthyears4 = 2005–2006 | youthclubs4 = Saint-Étienne du Rouvray | youthyears5 = 2006–2009 | youthclubs5 = [[CMS Oissel]] | youthyears6 = 2009–2015 | youthclubs6 = [[SM Caen]] | youthyears7 = 2015–2016 | youthclubs7 = [[Stade Rennais F.C.|Rennes]] | years1 = 2013–2014 | clubs1 = [[SM Caen|Caen B]] | caps1 = 18 | goals1 = 3 | years2 = 2015–2017 | clubs2 = [[Stade Rennais F.C.|Rennes B]] | caps2 = 15 | goals2 = 0 | years3 = 2016–2017 | clubs3 = [[Stade Rennais F.C.|Rennes]] | caps3 = 25 | goals3 = 4 | years4 = 2017–2018 | clubs4 = [[AS Monaco FC|Monaco]] | caps4 = 22 | goals4 = 2 | years5 = 2018– | clubs5 = [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]] | caps5 = 4 | goals5 = 0 | nationalyears1 = 2017– | nationalteam1 = [[France national under-21 football team|France U21]] | nationalcaps1 = 4 | nationalgoals1 = 0 | club-update = 08:56, 9 September 2018 (UTC) | nationalteam-update = 5 September 2017 }} '''Adama Salimou Diakhaby''' (born 5 July 1996) is a French professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a winger for [[Premier League]] club [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]].
==Club career== Diakhaby made his [[Ligue 1]] debut with [[Stade Rennais F.C.|Rennes]] on 14 August 2016 against [[OGC Nice]], replacing [[Giovanni Sio]] after 70 minutes.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lfp.fr/ligue1/feuille_match/81803|title=OGC Nice 1 - 0 Rennes|accessdate=14 August 2016|language=fr}}</ref> He scored his first Ligue 1 goal two weeks later away at [[Montpellier HSC]] to draw the game 1–1.
On 20 July 2018, Diakhaby joined [[Premier League]] club [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]] for an undisclosed fee on a three-year deal with the option of an additional year.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.htafc.com/news/2018/july/transfer-adama-diakhaby-arrives-from-as-monaco/|title=TRANSFER: ADAMA DIAKHABY ARRIVES FROM AS MONACO|publisher=[[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]]|date=20 July 2018|accessdate=20 July 2018}}</ref>
==International career== Of Senegalese descent, Diakhaby is eligible to play for Senegal and France.<ref>{{cite web|title=Découverte (Rennes): Adama Diakhaby, une graine de champion|url=http://www.galsenfoot.com/2016/07/21/decouverte-rennes-adama-diakhaby-une-graine-de-champion/|website=Galsenfoot|accessdate=14 March 2017|language=French|date=21 July 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170115074922/http://www.galsenfoot.com/2016/07/21/decouverte-rennes-adama-diakhaby-une-graine-de-champion/|archive-date=2017-01-15|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref>
