{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2011}} {{Infobox football biography | name = Christopher Schindler | image = Schindler, Christopher 1860 13-14 WP.JPG | image_size = 200 | caption = Schindler with [[TSV 1860 Munich|1860 Munich]] in 2013 | fullname = Christopher Wolfgang Georg August Schindler<ref>{{cite web |title=Squads for 2017/18 Premier League confirmed |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/465277 |publisher=Premier League |date=1 September 2017 |accessdate=9 September 2017}}</ref> | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1990|4|29|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Munich]], West Germany<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.worldfootball.net/spieler_profil/christopher-schindler/ | title = Christopher Schindler | publisher = worldfootball.net | accessdate = 30 July 2011}}</ref> | height = 1.89 m | position = [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|Centre-back]] | currentclub = [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]] | clubnumber = 26 | youthyears1 = 1999–2009 | youthclubs1 = [[TSV 1860 Munich|1860 Munich]] | years1 = 2009–2013 | clubs1 = [[TSV 1860 Munich II|1860 Munich II]] | caps1 = 32 | goals1 = 3 | years2 = 2010–2016 | clubs2 = [[TSV 1860 Munich|1860 Munich]] | caps2 = 152 | goals2 = 4 | years3 = 2016– | clubs3 = [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]] | caps3 = 110 | goals3 = 3 | nationalyears1 = 2011–2012 | nationalteam1 = [[Germany national under-21 football team|Germany U21]] | nationalcaps1 = 4 | nationalgoals1 = 0 | club-update = 23:25, 2 March 2019 (UTC) | nationalteam-update = }} '''Christopher Wolfgang Georg August Schindler''' ({{IPA-de|ˈkʀɪstɔfɐ ˈʃɪndlɐ}}; born 29 April 1990) is a German professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|centre-back]] for [[Premier League]] club [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]]. He has also played for [[Germany national under-21 football team|Germany U21]]s.
==Career== He was formerly the captain of his hometown team, [[TSV 1860 Munich]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/2bundesliga/vereine/2-bundesliga/2011-12/1860-muenchen-5/58074/spieler_schindler-christopher.html | title = Schindler, Christopher | language = German | publisher = kicker.de | accessdate = 30 July 2011}}</ref> He had been captaining the team since [[Julian Weigl]] was suspended to the second squad and fined for disciplinary reasons early in the [[2014–15 2. Bundesliga|2014–15 season]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.tz.de/sport/1860-muenchen/julian-weigl-1860-kapitaensbinde-dauerhaft-3776992.html | title = Weigl-Binde dauerhaft weg! Wer nun übernimmt | language = German | publisher = tz.de | accessdate = 13 August 2014}}</ref>
Schindler is a former Germany youth international, having played 4 games for the [[Germany national under-21 football team]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.weltfussball.de/spieler_profil/christopher-schindler/|title=Christopher Schindler|website=weltfussball.de}}</ref>
On 29 June 2016, Schindler joined English [[Football League Championship]] club [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]] for a then club record fee.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.htafc.com/news/2016/june/transfer-schindler-arrives-for-club-record-fee/|title=TRANSFER: SCHINDLER ARRIVES FOR CLUB RECORD FEE|website=www.htafc.com}}</ref> He made his debut for the Terriers in their 2–1 win over [[Brentford F.C.|Brentford]] on 6 August 2016. Schindler scored his first goal for the club in a 1–0 win over [[Ipswich Town]] on 1 October 2016.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/37460428|title=Ipswich 0–1 Huddersfield |publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|date=1 October 2016|accessdate=4 October 2016}}</ref>
On 29 May 2017, Schindler scored the winning penalty in the [[2017 EFL Championship play-off Final]] which took Huddersfield Town to the [[Premier League]] in a penalty shootout against [[Reading F.C.|Reading]].<ref>{{citeweb|url= https://www.theguardian.com/football/2017/may/29/huddersfield-reading-championship-play-off-final-match-report|title=Huddersfield reach Premier League after penalty shoot-out win over Reading|date=29 May 2017|work=Guardian|accessdate=31 May 2017}}</ref>
