{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2014}} {{Infobox football biography | name = Jon Gorenc Stanković | image = Jon Gorenc Stanković.jpg | image_size = | caption = | fullname = Jon Gorenc Stanković<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/612828 |title=Updated squads for 2017/18 Premier League confirmed |publisher=Premier League |date=2 February 2018 |accessdate=11 February 2018}}</ref> | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1996|01|14|df=y}}<ref name=BDFutbol>{{cite web |url=http://www.bdfutbol.com/en/j/j83070.html |title=Stanković: Jon Gorenc Stanković: Player |publisher=BDFutbol |accessdate=11 February 2018}}</ref> | birth_place = [[Ljubljana]], Slovenia<ref name=BDFutbol/> | height = 1.90 m<ref name=BDFutbol/> | position = [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|Centre back]] | currentclub = [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]] | clubnumber = 27 | youthyears1 = 2012–2014 | youthclubs1 = [[NK Domžale|Domžale]] | years1 = 2013–2016 | clubs1 = [[NK Domžale|Domžale]] | caps1 = 18 | goals1 = 0 | years2 = 2014–2016 | clubs2 = → [[Borussia Dortmund II]] (loan) | caps2 = 62 | goals2 = 1 | years3 = 2016– | clubs3 = [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]] | caps3 = 13 | goals3 = 1 | nationalyears1 = 2011–2012 | nationalteam1 = Slovenia U16 | nationalcaps1 = 9 | nationalgoals1 = 2 | nationalyears2 = 2012–2013 | nationalteam2 = [[Slovenia national under-17 football team|Slovenia U17]] | nationalcaps2 = 8 | nationalgoals2 = 0 | nationalyears3 = 2013 | nationalteam3 = Slovenia U18 | nationalcaps3 = 1 | nationalgoals3 = 0 | nationalyears4 = 2013–2014 | nationalteam4 = [[Slovenia national under-19 football team|Slovenia U19]] | nationalcaps4 = 10 | nationalgoals4 = 0 | nationalyears5 = 2015–2018 | nationalteam5 = [[Slovenia national under-21 football team|Slovenia U21]] | nationalcaps5 = 17 | nationalgoals5 = 2 | pcupdate = 16 March 2019 | ntupdate = }}
'''Jon Gorenc Stanković''' (born 14 January 1996) is a Slovenian [[Association football|football]] [[Defender (association football)|defender]] who plays for [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]] and the [[Slovenia national football team|Slovenian national team]].
==Club career==
===Huddersfield Town=== He made his debut for [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]] in an [[EFL Cup]] tie with [[Shrewsbury Town]] on 9 August 2016.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/36949806|title=Shrewsbury 2-1 Huddersfield|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|date=9 August 2016|accessdate=1 September 2016}}</ref> He made his league debut as a late substitute against [[Rotherham United]] on 27 September 2016.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/37414579|title=Huddersfield 2-1 Rotherham|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|date=27 September 2016|accessdate=6 October 2016}}</ref> He scored his first goal for Huddersfield Town on 19 August 2018 in a 6–1 defeat to [[Manchester City]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/45159602|title=Man City 6-1 Huddersfield: Sergio Aguero hat-trick as champions go top|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|date=19 August 2018|accessdate=20 August 2018}}</ref>
==International career== He was called up to the senior [[Slovenia national football team|Slovenia]] squad by [[Srečko Katanec]] for a friendly against [[Turkey national football team|Turkey]] in June 2016.<ref>{{cite news|title=V reprezentanci tudi Gorenc Stanković|url=http://ekipa24.si/clanek/nogomet/reprezentancni-nogomet/574464eea81ff/v-reprezentanci-tudi-gorenc-stankovic|accessdate=1 September 2016|publisher=ekipa24.si|date=24 May 2016}}</ref>
