{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2017}} {{Infobox football biography | name = Abdelhamid Sabiri | image = | caption = | fullname = Abdelhamid Sabiri<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/612828 |title=Updated squads for 2017/18 Premier League confirmed |publisher=Premier League |date=2 February 2018 |accessdate=11 February 2018}}</ref> | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1996|11|28|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Goulmima]], Morocco | height = 1.84 m | position = [[Midfielder]] | currentclub = [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]] | clubnumber = 29 | youthyears1 = {{0|0000}}–2014 | youthclubs1 = [[TuS Koblenz]] | youthyears2 = 2014–2015 | youthclubs2 = [[SV Darmstadt 98|Darmstadt 98]] | years1 = 2015–2016 | clubs1 = [[Sportfreunde Siegen]] | caps1 = 30 | goals1 = 18 | years2 = 2016–2017 | clubs2 = [[1. FC Nürnberg II]] | caps2 = 21 | goals2 = 12 | years3 = 2016–2017 | clubs3 = [[1. FC Nürnberg]] | caps3 = 9 | goals3 = 5 | years4 = 2017– | clubs4 = [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]] | caps4 = 7 | goals4 = 0 | nationalyears1 = 2018– | nationalteam1 = [[Germany national under-21 football team|Germany U21]] | nationalcaps1 = 3 | nationalgoals1 = 1 | club-update = 09:13, 9 September 2018 (UTC) | nationalteam-update = 20:16, 19 November 2018 (UTC) }} '''Abdelhamid Sabiri''' (born 28 November 1996) is a Moroccan-born German [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for {{English football updater|HuddersT}} club [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]].
==Early life== He was born in Morocco and came to Germany when he was three years old. There he was raised in [[Frankfurt]] and holds dual citizenship of Germany and Morocco.<ref>{{cite web|title=Sabiri spielt für Mamas Miete|url=http://www.bild.de/sport/fussball/1-fc-nuernberg/sabiri-spielt-fuer-mamas-miete-52516750.bild.html|website=bild.de|language=German|date=11 July 2017|accessdate=23 August 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title= Huddersfield seal 11th summer signing as No.10 Abdelhamid Sabiri joins from Nurnberg |url=http://www.squawka.com/news/huddersfield-seal-summer-signing-as-no-10-abdelhamid-sabiri-joins-from-nurnberg/983498|website=squawka.com|date=23 August 2017|accessdate=23 August 2017}}</ref>
==Club career== ===Huddersfield Town=== Sabiri made his [[Premier League]] debut for [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]] in their away game fixture against [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham]] on 11 September 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.footballfallout.com/premier-league-2017-2018/game/west-ham-united-vs-huddersfield-town-11-09-2017|title=West Ham United v Huddersfield Town|website=Football Fallout|language=en|access-date=12 September 2017}}</ref>
==International career== Sabiri was called up to [[Germany national under-21 football team|Germany's under-21 side]] in October 2018.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.examinerlive.co.uk/sport/football/news/you-can-see-seven-huddersfield-15283797|title=When you can see SEVEN Town internationals in action tomorrow|last=Benson|first=Rory|date=15 October 2018|work=Huddersfield Examiner|access-date=15 October 2018}}</ref>
