{{Infobox football biography | name = Florent Hadergjonaj | image = YB vs. FCL - Hadergjonaj 3.jpg | fullname = Florent Hadergjonaj<ref>{{cite web |title=Squads for 2017/18 Premier League confirmed |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/465277 |publisher=Premier League |date=1 September 2017 |accessdate=9 September 2017}}</ref> | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1994|7|31|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Langnau im Emmental|Langnau]], Switzerland | height = {{height|m=1.82}} | position = [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|Right-back]] | currentclub = [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]] | clubnumber = 33 | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = FC Langnau | youthyears2 = 2007–2010 | youthclubs2 = [[FC Thun]] | youthyears3 = 2010–2011 | youthclubs3 = [[FC Luzern]] | youthyears4 = 2011–2013 | youthclubs4 = [[BSC Young Boys|Young Boys]] | years1 = 2013–2016 | clubs1 = [[BSC Young Boys|Young Boys]] | caps1 = 71 | goals1 = 0 | years2 = 2016–2018 | clubs2 = [[FC Ingolstadt 04|Ingolstadt 04]] | caps2 = 27 | goals2 = 1 | years3 = 2017–2018 | clubs3 = → [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]] (loan) | caps3 = 23 | goals3 = 0 | years4 = 2018– | clubs4 = [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]] | caps4 = 19 | goals4 = 0 | pcupdate = 09:43, 3 January 2019 (UTC) | nationalyears1 = 2013–2014 | nationalteam1 = [[Switzerland national under-20 football team|Switzerland U20]] | nationalcaps1 = 2 | nationalgoals1 = 0 | nationalyears2 = 2014–2016 | nationalteam2 = [[Switzerland national under-21 football team|Switzerland U21]] | nationalcaps2 = 8 | nationalgoals2 = 0 | nationalyears3 = 2017– | nationalteam3 = [[Switzerland national football team|Switzerland]] | nationalcaps3 = 1 | nationalgoals3 = 0 | ntupdate = 5 June 2017 }} '''Florent Hadergjonaj''' ({{IPA-sq|hadeɾɟoˈnaj}}; born 31 July 1994) is a Swiss professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)|right-back]] for [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]] in the [[Premier League]]; initially on loan from [[FC Ingolstadt 04|Ingolstadt]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/bundesliga/vereine/657626/artikel_hadergjonaj-wird-ein-schanzer.html|title=Hadergjonaj wird ein Schanzer|first=kicker, Nürnberg,|last=Germany|publisher=}}</ref><ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=https://www.htafc.com/news/2017/august/loan-florent-hadergjonaj-joins-htafc/|title=Huddersfield Town LOAN: FLORENT HADERGJONAJ JOINS HTAFC|access-date=2017-08-24|language=en-gb}}</ref> Hadergjonaj signed a three-year contract in July 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/43327734}}</ref>
==Club career== Hadergjonaj is a youth exponent from [[BSC Young Boys]]. He made his [[Swiss Super League]] debut on 29 September 2013 against [[FC Zürich]] in 0–1 home defeat.<ref name="soccerway2">{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2013/09/29/switzerland/super-league/bsc-young-boys-bern/fc-zurich/1481227/|title=Young Boys vs. FC Zürich - 29 September 2013 - Soccerway|publisher=soccerway.com|accessdate=2014-08-26}}</ref> He made 11 league appearances during the 2013–14 season. He won the BSC Young Boys player of the year award after 1 year and a half from his debut.
On 8 August 2016, Hadergjonaj penned a four-year deal with FC Ingolstadt 04.<ref>{{cite web|title=Hadergjonaj zu Ingolstadt, Joss zurück zu YB|url=http://www.bernerzeitung.ch/sport/fussball/joss-kehrt-zu-yb-zurueck-hadergjonaj-geht-zu-ingolstadt/story/16133181|publisher=Berner Zeitung|accessdate=29 August 2016|language=German|date=8 August 2016}}</ref>
On 24 August 2017, Hadergjonaj was signed on a season long loan by [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]], with the club purchasing the young Swiss during the January transfer season (2018).<ref name=":0" />
